## 6. Subscriber semantics `[E-D3: Strict + auto-add del URL]`

### 6.1 Flujo `ckl aether subscribe <url>`

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Usuario
    participant CLI as ckl
    participant Trust as TrustStore
    participant HTTP as HTTP layer
    participant Store as AetherStore

    U->>CLI: ckl aether subscribe https://.../ckl-internals/
    CLI->>HTTP: fetch pkg/manifest.json
    HTTP-->>CLI: manifest + publisher_cert
    CLI->>Trust: verify cert against trust anchors
    Trust-->>CLI: ok (KOSLAB anchor matches)

    Note over CLI: Auto-add publisher a allowlist (E-D3)
    CLI->>Store: Intent::SetPublisherAllowlist { publisher: "koslab", action: Allow }

    CLI->>Store: Intent::UpsertSource { kind: Aether, project_id: None, name: "<package>", url: "..." }
    Store-->>CLI: source_id + auto-bound entity_id (per entity en manifest)

    CLI-->>U: Subscribed. Run `ckl aether sync` to pull.
```

### 6.2 Modos disponibles

| Mode | Comportamiento | CLI flag |
|---|---|---|
| **Strict + auto-add** (default) | Solo accept publishers en allowlist; subscribe añade automáticamente | (sin flag) |
| **Strict puro** | Solo accept publishers en allowlist; subscribe NO añade (usuario debe `ckl aether trust add` previo) | `--no-auto-trust` |
| **Open** | Accept cualquier publisher cuya cert valide contra anchors | `--mode open` (advertencia visible) |

### 6.3 Cross-publisher edges en Strict default

- Edges de `koslab` que apuntan a `acme-research` (no allowed) llegan como `PendingEdge` (ya shipped Área C/H3).
- Si usuario después hace `ckl aether subscribe https://acme-research/...`, el cascade resolver natural (BL-1 + E-D5) las promueve a `LocalRelationship`.
- Si nunca llega → expira por TTL (`pending_edge_ttl_secs`, ya shipped).

